Q:

How to get raw stdin data in C?

I have a file with "line" (wchar_t*) strings and I want to be able to read all the contents of a line.
Is there a way to do this in C?

A:

You need to use fgets() and getline() to read the data in a line.
#include <stdio.h>

int main(void)
{
    FILE* fout = fopen("foo.txt", "w+");

    if (fout == NULL)
    {
        fprintf(stderr, "Unable to open file for writing: %s\n", strerror(errno));
        return -1;
    }

    fgets(buffer, sizeof buffer, fout);
    fclose(fout);

    return 0;
}

The buffer will be a pointer to a buffer of characters read from the file.
Note that fgets() should be used in conjunction with getline() for this to work correctly.  getline() will return the next line from the input stream (or will read until the end of file is reached).  fgets() will read every character until the end of file is reached.

